    "body": "## Motivation\r\nFixes #24637.\r\n`test/registered/mla/test_flashmla.py` currently forces the FlashMLA MTP speculative decoding test to fall back to spec decoding v1 by setting `SGLANG_ENABLE_SPEC_V2=False`. FlashMLA should support spec decoding v2 and the registered CUDA CI test should cover that path explicitly.\r\n## Modifications\r\n- Enable spec decoding v2 in `TestFlashMLAMTP` by changing `SGLANG_ENABLE_SPEC_V2.override(False)` to `SGLANG_ENABLE_SPEC_V2.override(True)`.\r\n- Treat `ForwardMode.DRAFT_EXTEND_V2` as a speculative draft-extend mode in DeepSeek MLA attention backend dispatch.\r\n- Route FlashMLA `DRAFT_EXTEND_V2` forward calls through the extend/prefill path instead of the target-verify FlashMLA path, matching the existing metadata initialization behavior.\r\n## Accuracy Tests\r\nLocal syntax checks passed:\r\n```bash\r\npython3 -m py_compile python/sglang/srt/layers/attention/flashmla_backend.py\r\npython3 -m py_compile python/sglang/srt/models/deepseek_v2.py\r\npython3 -m py_compile test/registered/mla/test_flashmla.py\r\nLocal formatting and lint checks passed with the same tool versions configured in .pre-commit-config.yaml:\r\nuvx --from isort==7.0.0 isort \\\r\n  python/sglang/srt/layers/attention/flashmla_backend.py \\\r\n  python/sglang/srt/models/deepseek_v2.py \\\r\n  test/registered/mla/test_flashmla.py\r\nuvx --from ruff==0.15.1 ruff check --select=F401,F821 --fix \\\r\n  python/sglang/srt/layers/attention/flashmla_backend.py \\\r\n  python/sglang/srt/models/deepseek_v2.py \\\r\n  test/registered/mla/test_flashmla.py\r\nuvx --from black==26.1.0 black \\\r\n  python/sglang/srt/layers/attention/flashmla_backend.py \\\r\n  python/sglang/srt/models/deepseek_v2.py \\\r\n  test/registered/mla/test_flashmla.py\r\nFull FlashMLA spec-v2 accuracy validation requires a FlashMLA-capable CUDA GPU. It is covered by the stage-b-test-1-gpu-large CI suite, which runs on 1-gpu-h100.\r\nSpeed Tests and Profiling\r\nNot run. This PR enables the existing FlashMLA spec-v2 path in CI and does not introduce a new kernel or intended performance optimization.\r\nChecklist\r\n- [x] Format your code according to the Format code with pre-commit (https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#format-code-with-pre-commit).\r\n- [x] Add unit tests according to the Run and add unit tests (https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#run-and-add-unit-tests).\r\n- [ ] Update documentation according to Write documentations (https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#write-documentations).\r\n- [ ] Provide accuracy and speed benchmark results according to Test the accuracy (https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#test-the-accuracy) and Benchmark the speed (https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#benchmark-the-speed).\r\n- [x] Follow the SGLang code style guidance (https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#code-style-guidance).\r\nReview and Merge Process\r\n1. Ping Merge Oncalls to start the process. See the PR Merge Process (https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/blob/main/.github/MAINTAINER.md#pull-request-merge-process).\r\n2. Get approvals from CODEOWNERS (https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/blob/main/.github/CODEOWNERS) and other reviewers.\r\n3. Trigger CI tests with comments (https://docs.sglang.io/developer_guide/contribution_guide.html#how-to-trigger-ci-tests) or contact authorized users to do so.\r\n   - Common commands include /tag-and-rerun-ci, /tag-run-ci-label, /rerun-failed-ci\r\n4. After green CI and required approvals, ask Merge Oncalls or people with Write permission to merge the PR.\n\n\n\n\n\n<!-- pr-states:start -->\n---\n### CI States\n\nLatest PR Test (Base): <!-- slot:pr-test:start -->[Run #26009417065](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/actions/runs/26009417065)<!-- slot:pr-test:end -->\nLatest PR Test (Extra): <!-- slot:pr-test-extra:start -->:warning: **Not enabled** — add `run-ci-extra` label to opt in.<!-- slot:pr-test-extra:end -->\n<!-- pr-states:end -->",
